The Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) presidential candidate and former Vice President, Atiku Abubakar,  has picked the former Anambra state governor, Peter Obi, as his running mate. Atiku and Obi had earlier gone into a closed-door meeting at Mr Atiku’s residence at about 3:30pm before the announcement was made. The Former Vice President was on Thursday endorsed by former President Olusegun Obasanjo, when he met the latter in Abeokuta, the Ogun State capital, on Thursday. The ruling All Progressive Congress (APC) has endorsed President Muhammadu Buhari to run for second time in office. 